priest spells on bandits, but not saying the don't drop there. Tarmoks used to drop spells before they lowered their levels.<P><BR><B>Umbral Plains</B><BR>Believe any mob has an <B>extremely</B> rare chance of dropping a spell. Have seen 1 spell in several hundred kills of various mobs. Believe it was a lower level one too, a la Fungus Grove.<P><B>Akheva Ruins</B><BR>Hybrid spells - Mind worms<P><B>Ssrashaeza (sp) Temple</B><BR>Believe any non-patroller, non-elite guard mob can drop any spell on the first floor. In the basement we found the drop rate to be much better. Straight across from where you come down, on the other side of the middle of the room, is a temple-like structure. Immediately at the top of the stairs to the right and left are two statics. Straight ahead is some large rooms with lots of statics. Spells were a lot more common there, since every mob could drop a spell.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=191031" TARGET=_blank>Viscera Galen</A><BR>L60 High Priest of Brell<BR><A HREF="http://www.darktemplarsguild.co.uk" TARGET=_blank>Dark Templars</A><BR>Xegony<p>[This message has been edited by Viscera (edited 05-23-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Battlecups</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Epitaph of Life dropped fer me in Umbral Plains off a Disturbed Elysian Remains ... but i hafta think it was a rare drop. My guildmates seemed surprised a spell dropped (that and the two doodads were hoping fer armor hehe).<P><BR>Hello der Viscera. Good to see ye again, brother Cleric. Say Hello to Kildaan and Darek for me...<P>Oh and ding 49. Finally getting back up to my old self!<BR><P>------------------<BR>Thortak Ironhelm<BR>Cleric and Professional Stout Dispenser<BR>Proud Member of the Warders of Truth on Xegony</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
